Session `03_image_based_surface_estimation` adds
`estimate_surface_and_l2_image_based()` in
`code/dev_code/03_image_based_surface.py`.  Tile-wise intensity-jump
detection → IRLS-Huber plane for pia; parallel-plane fit for L2.
Driver + figures in `03_image_based_surface_run.py` /
`03_image_based_surface_figs.py`; results in
`sessions/03_image_based_surface_estimation/`.

**Why:** User asked for a purely image-intensity approach with L2
added.  CZ L2 uses background-only (segmentation_mask == 0) as
instructed.  Distribution-driven thresholds: baseline from truly-blank
top slices (≤5 % of dyn_hint) with dynamic-range fallback when the blank
pool is too small.

**How to apply:** Treat it as *complementary* to N22, not a
replacement.  CZ surface here is near-perfect (resid MAD ≤ 1.3 µm,
above_frac ≈ 0).  HCR surface is looser (MAD 32–120 µm); for HCR pia,
`analyze_subject` with `quantile_ceiling` (N22) remains the default.

**Open issues (2026-04-17):** CZ L2 floors at `min_l1=40 µm` on 4/6
subjects because bg-only L1 window is too sparse — next try
segmentation-density jump instead of bg intensity.  HCR above_frac
3–7 % (vs N22 ≤0.08 %) — per-tile adaptive threshold may close the gap.
